    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-07-21T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-07-21T18:00:00-05:00" n="770"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d770">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.00/665: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-21T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >July 21, 1931—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:18 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>70. Blanquier Cabinet, differing with the President over its program of greater
                    political freedom and retrenchment, has resigned and resignation has been
                    accepted. Rumors suggest men for new cabinet who are closer to President
                    personally but who will command less confidence from public. Fear is expressed
                    that break-down of Blanquier program will be followed by political trouble from
                    which may come new leader, and by further economic difficulties including
                    depreciation of currency.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Culbertson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
